		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Pythagorean tuning</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Pythagorean tuning</b> is a system of <a href="/wiki/Musical_tuning" title="Musical tuning">musical tuning</a> in which the <a href="/wiki/Frequency" title="Frequency">frequency</a> relationships of all <a href="/wiki/Interval_(music)" title="Interval (music)">intervals</a> are based on the ratio <a href="/wiki/Sesquialterum" title="Sesquialterum" class="mw-redirect">3:2</a>. Its name comes from medieval texts which attribute its discovery to <a href="/wiki/Pythagoras" title="Pythagoras">Pythagoras</a>, but its use has been documented as long ago as 3500 B.C. in Babylonian texts.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> It is the oldest way of tuning the 12-note <a href="/wiki/Chromatic_scale" title="Chromatic scale">chromatic scale</a>.</p>
<p><span class="unicode" style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/File:Pythagorean_diatonic_scale.mid" title="File:Pythagorean diatonic scale.mid"><img alt="Pythagorean diatonic scale.mid" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" border="0" /></a> <a href="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/c9/Pythagorean_diatonic_scale.mid" class="internal" title="Pythagorean diatonic scale.mid">play diatonic scale in Pythagorean tuning</a> <small class="metadata audiolinkinfo">(<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Media_help" title="Wikipedia:Media help">help</a>·<a href="/wiki/File:Pythagorean_diatonic_scale.mid" title="File:Pythagorean diatonic scale.mid">info</a>)</small></span> <span class="unicode" style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/File:Diatonic_scale_on_C.mid" title="File:Diatonic scale on C.mid"><img alt="Diatonic scale on C.mid" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" border="0" /></a> <a href="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/31/Diatonic_scale_on_C.mid" class="internal" title="Diatonic scale on C.mid">contrast with diatonic scale in 12-et</a> <small class="metadata audiolinkinfo">(<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Media_help" title="Wikipedia:Media help">help</a>·<a href="/wiki/File:Diatonic_scale_on_C.mid" title="File:Diatonic scale on C.mid">info</a>)</small></span> <span class="unicode" style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/File:Just_diatonic_scale_on_C.mid" title="File:Just diatonic scale on C.mid"><img alt="Just diatonic scale on C.mid" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" border="0" /></a> <a href="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/a1/Just_diatonic_scale_on_C.mid" class="internal" title="Just diatonic scale on C.mid">contrast with just diatonic scale</a> <small class="metadata audiolinkinfo">(<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Media_help" title="Wikipedia:Media help">help</a>·<a href="/wiki/File:Just_diatonic_scale_on_C.mid" title="File:Just diatonic scale on C.mid">info</a>)</small></span></p>
